name: Puzzel Face
description:
"Puzzel Face," 2022, JPEG
This was an experiment I created in 2016.  This was a time when "identity" was all the rage.  Every art exhibition or art fair filled rooms with art about topics about the self and identity.  It was a time when the internet was a mirror.  When social media made us look at ourselves in selfies, made humanity look at itself through shared images and media on a global scale.  But in the art world, you really felt a turn to look back at ourselves, into the artist's psyche and internal world.  I was afraid we might get stuck there to be honest.
